comments.content:
My comment about Alias was because I see a lot of David James & Gareth Hague’s intutions (but others as well) in letterforms picked up by the designer(s?) of Textaxis.  
For example, the typeface Borneo has a lot of forms influenced by Alias’ MetSys (which, in turn, was based on James’ lettering for the early 1990s album covers of Steve Hillage’s band System 7).  
Inercia and Suite owe a lot to FF Dax (1995-1997) and the previous Barmeno (1983) by Hans Reichel;  
Oneline is heavily influenced by Alias’ Progress (2002);  
Latina Italic owes an lot (in terms of stylization) to John Downer’s Triplex (1985), and so on…
